definitions.definition: To give birth to or produce (as its female parent) a child . ( Compare father . )
To treat as a mother would be expected to treat her child; to nurture .
To cause to contain mother ( “ that substance which develops in fermenting alcohol and turns it into vinegar ” ) .
examples: mothered oil , mothered vinegar , mothered wine

main_definition: ( chiefly transitive ) To give birth to or produce (as its female parent) a child . ( Compare father . )
secondary_definitions: ( transitive ) To treat as a mother would be expected to treat her child; to nurture .
( transitive ) To cause to contain mother ( “ that substance which develops in fermenting alcohol and turns it into vinegar ” ) .
( intransitive , of an alcohol ) To develop mother.
